<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910617-0125</DOCNO><DOCID>910617-0125.</DOCID><HL>   Ferro to Sell Some Assets</HL><DATE>06/17/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B5</SO><CO>   FOE MNT</CO><MS>BASIC MATERIALS (BSC)CONGLOMERATES (CGL)</MS><IN>CHEMICALS, PLASTICS (CHM)TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)</IN><NS>ACQUISITIONS andamp; MERGERS, TAKEOVERS, BOARD BATTLES (TNM)</NS><RE>CALIFORNIA (CA)EUROPE (EU)ITALY (ITA)NORTH AMERICA (NME)OHIO (OH)PACIFIC RIM (PRM)UNITED STATES (US)WESTERN EUROPE (WEU)</RE><LP>   CLEVELAND -- Ferro Corp. said it signed an agreement tosell its Los Angeles-based composites business to asubsidiary of Montecatini, which is the technology arm ofMontedison S.p.A.   The sale will result in a charge of $1 million, or fivecents a share, in the second quarter.</LP><TEXT>   Montecatini, of Milan, Italy, is involved in thematerials, pharmaceutical and energy areas. Ferro makesindustrial specialty materials.</TEXT></DOC>